Police are looking for a gang that carjacked a matatu and robbed passengers along Jogoo Road on Wednesday night. The matatu was headed for Donholm when four men boarded it at Landhies road near the City Stadium. They immediately started to rob passengers. The gang later alighted along Jogoo Road and escaped on foot. A woman who tried to resist was hit in the head and injured. Elsewhere a suspected thug was shot dead in Buruburu. The suspect was in the company of three others and were attacking and robbing pedestrians. In Parklands, another a suspected thug was lynched by a mob after he was caught robbing a supermarket in the area. Read: Suspected thug shot dead in Kayole, 3 escape Click here for the latest political news